isRelevantFor

protected boolean isRelevantFor(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject eObject,
                                org.eclipse.core.resources.IMarker marker)
                         throws org.eclipse.core.runtime.CoreException
Defines if marker is relevant for eObject. Only for web method and web parameter we need to define if the marker is relevant because they are not unique in the scope of the resource. For example if there is a marker set on the resource containing SEI, the SEI should be marked in any case while the method only in case when the error is specifically for this method or method parameter.

Parameters:
eObject - the object to be validated
marker - the resource marker
Returns:
true in case the marker is relevant for eObject
Throws:
org.eclipse.core.runtime.CoreException

                               throws org.eclipse.core.runtime.CoreException
Defines if marker is relevant for webMethod. Checks if the marker is specifically for this method or some of it's parameters.

Parameters:
